    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-03-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-03-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="560"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d560">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_CC2" type="from"
                            >Churchill</persName> to President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1" type="to"
                            >Roosevelt</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d560fn1">Sent by the United States Military Attaché, London,
                        via Army channels.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-03-07">7 March
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>No. 608. Prime Minister to President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1"
                        >Roosevelt</persName> personal and most secret. About the Italian ships.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>I have never agreed nor have you ever asked me to agree to a division of
                        the Italian Fleet into 3 shares. If this claim were to be based on the fact
                        that we 3 Powers signed the Italian Armistice together, what about all the
                        other Powers that fought Italy? Greece for instance would have an
                        irrefutable claim. It was not until after the Cairo conference that I heard
                        you had mentioned about the ⅓ for Russia. <persName corresp="#p_HWA2"
                            >Averell</persName> was however able to assure you that nothing of the
                        sort had been said to the Russians. See your number 437.<note n="2"
                            xml:id="d560fn2">
                            <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_866">p. 866</ref>.</note>
                        You are therefore quite uncommitted so far as they are concerned.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>His Majesty’s Government would not be able to agree to a division of the
                        Italian Fleet by ⅓ or a pro rata division among signatories to the
                        Armistice.…</item>
                </list>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <list>
                    <label>5.</label>
                    <item>At the Moscow conference the Russians asked for certain specified types of
                        Italian ships, namely <list>
                            <item>1 Battleship</item>
                            <item>1 Cruiser</item>
                            <item>8 Destroyers</item>
                            <item>4 Submarines</item>
                            <item>and 40,000 tons of merchant shipping.</item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <p rend="flushleft">At Teheran we assented to this.…</p>
            </div>
